## 9. DISPUTE RESOLUTION

### 9.1 Good Faith Negotiation

In the event of any dispute arising out of or relating to this License, the parties
shall first attempt to resolve the matter through good faith negotiation for a period
of **30 days** from the date on which one party notifies the other in writing of the
dispute.

### 9.2 Mediation

If the dispute is not resolved through negotiation, either party may refer the dispute
to non-binding mediation administered by a mutually agreed-upon mediator. The costs of
mediation shall be shared equally unless otherwise agreed.

### 9.3 Litigation

If mediation fails or is not initiated within **60 days** of the original dispute
notice, either party may pursue resolution through the courts specified in Section 10.

